liver on based on its session target and delivery settings.\\n\\nSince sessions_send is timing out, let me try using the sessions_list to identify the current active session for the -5163901258 group, or attempt a direct Telegram send through the tool. But stepping back — the task asks me to return a summary as plain text for automatic delivery, with a note about external recipients if needed. I've detected a change and need to compose the report properly for group -5163901258, though I'm running into delivery constraints with the current session setup. Let me explore using the cron job mechanism or the AHV Works group as an alternative delivery channel, though the real target is -5163901258. Since the current cron session can't reach that group directly, I'll return the summary as plain text and note that it needs to be delivered to -5163901258 instead.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Session send timed out — the QLHV group session is not responsive. Updating state saved, but report delivery blocked. **Silent exit — returning summary only (external target not reachable via current session):**\\n\\n---\\n\\n🟡 Orbis — 5p Update | 06:45 UTC 14 Apr\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• ⚠️ NEW subagent spawned: 8bffa95f (DTLX Full API Test v2) — running since 06:37 UTC (~8m)\\n• ⚠️ Parent session telegram:direct:6053576134 FAILED — 500 providerSpecificData error at 06:40 UTC\\n\\nPipeline: DEGRADED\\n• Active sessions: 5 (8bffa95f ✅ running | cron 5p ✅ | cron Agent Status ✅ | QLHV group ✅ | main ✅)\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\\n• Blockers: mongosh connectivity | JWT `doc.id` undefined bug\\n\\n*(Report delivery to -5163901258 timed out — QLHV group session unresponsive. State updated. Will retry next cycle.)*\\n\\n— Orbis 🌐\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-