 the pipeline is stable and the changes are noted in state. The Lead direct session failed but it spawned a new subagent that's working. No alerts needed."},{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":143,"output":50,"totalTokens":42131,"cacheRead":39225,"cacheWrite":2713,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776149287298,"responseId":"062d16289fbf6434a9d51792f253d9c8","__openclaw":{"id":"2c3bd824","seq":80}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","origin":{"provider":"heartbeat"},"label":"Cron: 5p Progress Report","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1776149149454,"sessionId":"81d6786b-23ea-456b-9aad-2dde68efbd63","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":45810,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776132125620,"endedAt":1776134758604,"runtimeMs":114127,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/81d6786b-23ea-456b-9aad-2dde68efbd63.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me send the report to group -5163901258. I'll compose a concise change report."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jcpbrci1zrbk_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258","message":"🟡 Orbis — 5p Update | 06:45 UTC 14 Apr\n\nChanges detected:\n• ⚠️ NEW subagent spawned: 8bffa95f (DTLX Full API Test v2) — running since 06:37 UTC (~8m)\n• ⚠️ Parent session telegram:direct:6053576134 FAILED — 500 providerSpecificData error at 06:40 UTC\n\nPipeline: DEGRADED\n• Active sessions: 5\n  - 8bffa95f (DTLX Full API Test v2) ✅ running\n  - cron: 5p Progress Report ✅ running\n  - cron: Agent Status to Lead ✅ running\n  - QLHV group session ✅ running\n  - master-orchestrator:main ✅ running\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\n• Blockers: mongosh connectivity | JWT `doc.id` undefined bug\n\n— Orbis 🌐","timeoutSeconds":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":153,"output":301,"totalTokens":45736,"cacheRead":43097,"cacheWrite":2185,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776149312656,"responseId":"062d1641a2326766d3b855ce3c9f2c06","__openclaw":{"id":"4a9efc66","seq":9}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session_send timed out. The report couldn't be delivered to the group. This is a known issue with the QLHV ecosystem group session being slow. Let me try the main telegram direct session or use the cron delivery mechanism.\n\nActually, looking at the session history, the QLHV group session (8e0cb2bc) ended at 06:32 UTC. The current group session might be a new one. Let me check if there's a current active group session.\n\nActually the session_key \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258\" returned a timeout. This could mean the session is in a bad state. Let me try to use a different approach - maybe the cron job delivery mode handles this differently.\n\n\nThe cron job delivery configures the target as \"current\" session, but this cron is running as a one-shot in a separate isolated session, so the delivery would route back to this cron session itself rather than the QLHV group. I should try the AHV Works group session at -5212380728 instead, or reconsider the approach since the delivery mode is configured for \"current\" which doesn't match what we need here.\n\nActually, looking at the Telegram group session status — it shows \"running\" with an endedAt timestamp, which indicates the parent session died. The cron job that spawned this work is a subagent, so I need to figure out what channel it was actually configured to deliver on based on its session target and delivery settings.\n\nSince sessions_send is timing out, let me try using the sessions_list to identify the current active session for the -5163901258 group, or attempt a direct Telegram send through the tool. But stepping back — the task asks me to return a summary as plain text for automatic delivery, with a note about external recipients if needed. I've detected a change and need to compose the report properly for group -5163901258, though I'm running into delivery constraints with the current session setup. Let me explore using the cron job mechanism or the AHV Works group as an alternative delivery channel, though the real target is -5163901258. Since the current cron session can't reach that group directly, I'll return the summary as plain text and note that it needs to be delivered to -5163901258 instead."},{"type":"text","text":"Session send timed out — the QLHV group session is not responsive. Updating state saved, but report delivery blocked. **Silent exit — returning summary only (external target not reachable via current session):**\n\n---\n\n🟡 Orbis — 5p Update | 06:45 UTC 14 Apr\n\nChanges detected:\n• ⚠️ NEW subagent spawned: 8bffa95f (DTLX Full API Test v2) — running since 06:37 UTC (~8m)\n• ⚠️ Parent session telegram:direct:6053576134 FAILED — 500 providerSpecificData error at 06:40 UTC\n\nPipeline: DEGRADED\n• Active sessions: 5 (8bffa95f ✅ running | cron 5p ✅ | cron Agent Status ✅ | QLHV group ✅ | main ✅)\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\n• Blockers: mongosh connectivity | JWT `doc.id` undefined bug\n\n*(Report delivery to -5163901258 timed out — QLHV group session unresponsive. State updated. Will retry next cycle.)*\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":179,"output":722,"totalTokens":46532,"cacheRead":43643,"cacheWrite":1988,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776149353728,"responseId":"062d166b636d6314508f0e8d41e62595","__openclaw":{"id":"cca3705b","seq":11}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:5d2b77de-dd66-41c2-b053-30aabd324a0e","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","label":"DTLX Full API Test + Seed","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-subagent-5d2b77de-dd66-41c2-b053-30aabd324a0e","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1776142955056,"sessionId":"c8fccefe-9951-44cf-b292-b5b8ca77a0cf","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":34167,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"failed","startedAt":1776142852138,"endedAt":1776143118533,"runtimeMs":164345,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/c8fccefe-9951-44cf-b292-b5b8ca77a0cf.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It seems the collections don't exist or are empty. Let me check what collections exist in the database:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dw84pej6u7nt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mongosh \"mongodb://localhost:27017/ahv_dtlx\" --quiet --eval \"\ndb.getCollectionNames().forEach(function(c) { print(c); });\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":103,"output":82,"totalTokens":34149,"cacheRead":33216,"cacheWrite":748,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776143067851,"responseId":"062cfddc10fd38fe299cbafb8cb180d6","__openclaw":{"id":"c4362291","seq":70}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It seems mongosh might not be available or the database connection is different. Let me check:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wpt5k1bnm0z3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which mongosh mongo 2>/dev/null; mongosh --version 2>/dev/null; mongo --version 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wpt5k1bnm0z3_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/config/database.ts 2>/dev/null || cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/.env 2>/dev/null | grep -i mongo | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":103,"output":160,"totalTokens":34327,"cacheRead":33786,"cacheWrite":278,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776143078585,"responseId":"062cfde71d5ac410f718cc52b0203c0d","__openclaw":{"id":"ede613bc","seq":72}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:53ffecba-7a14-43e4-91be-9b3efcc56072","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","label":"DTLX BE Start & Test","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-subagent-53ffecba-7a14-43e4-91be-9b3efcc56072","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1776142006662,"sessionId":"da8cc51e-e69c-4441-b358-faff21dd6739","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":34224,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1776141563990,"endedAt":1776141938964,"runtimeMs":351405,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/da8cc51e-e69c-4441-b358-faff21dd6739.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no `/users/me` endpoint. The `/users/:id` endpoint requires auth. And there's no `/auth/profile` endpoint either.\n\nLet me also check the `/guests` endpoint since it doesn't require auth (it's mounted before the global auth middleware).\n\nLet me test the guests endpoint to verify it works without auth."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fhuhri8bmqei_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3001/api/v1/guests"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":528,"output":105,"totalTokens":34147,"cacheRead":33103,"cacheWrite":411,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776141897929,"responseId":"062cf94b9cb648b4d6eb99f95d35c2f1","__openclaw":{"id":"8bb4e790","seq":98}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Guests endpoint works without auth. Now let me also test the ping endpoint.\n\nLet me also check the /docs endpoint for Swagger UI.\n\nNow let me summarize what I've found:\n\n1. **Server Status**: Already running on ports 3001 (HTTP) and 5557 (Socket IO)\n2. **MongoDB**: Connected (docker-proxy on 27017)\n3. **Auth API**:\n   - ✅ `POST /api/v1/auth/signin` - Works perfectly. Returns JWT tokens (access + refresh)\n   - ❌ `POST /api/v1/auth/register` - **Does NOT exist** in the codebase\n   - ❌ `GET /api/v1/auth/profile` - **Does NOT exist** in the codebase\n4. **Guests API** (no auth required):\n   - ✅ `GET /api/v1/guests` - Works (empty list)\n5. **Protected endpoints**: All require auth (401 returned without token)\n\nThere's a bug in the token generation where `doc.id` is undefined for Mongoose lean docs, causing the `id` field to be omitted from JWT tokens. This prevents protected endpoints from working with the generated tokens, so the profile endpoint can't be tested. The auth middleware issue is a known bug where the `doc.id` field is undefined in lean queries, causing protected endpoints to fail. The register and profile endpoints don't actually exist in the codebase—the API only has signin available, so I'll document what I actually found rather than trying to force tests for non-existent routes."},{"type":"text","text":"## Test Results Summary\n\n### ✅ Server Status\n| Component | Status |\n|-----------|--------|\n| HTTP Server | Running on **port 3001** |\n| Socket.IO | Running on **port 5557** |\n| MongoDB | Connected (docker-proxy on 27017) |\n\n### ✅ Auth — `POST /api/v1/auth/signin`\n**Works perfectly.** Login with existing user `admin2`:\n```\nPOST /api/v1/auth/signin\nBody: {\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Admin123!\"}\n\n→ 200 OK\n→ Returns: accessToken, refreshToken, user doc, permissions\n```\n\n### ✅ Guests — `GET /api/v1/guests` (no auth)\n**Works perfectly.** Returns empty guest list (correct).\n\n### ❌ `POST /api/v1/auth/register` — **NOT FOUND**\nThis endpoint **does not exist** in the codebase. The auth routes only have:\n- `POST /auth/signin` (login)\n- `PATCH /auth/change-password` (requires token)\n- `POST /auth/refetch-token` (requires token)\n\nNo user registration endpoint exists — users must be created by an admin via `POST /api/v1/users`.\n\n### ❌ `GET /api/v1/auth/profile` — **NOT FOUND**\nNo `/auth/profile` endpoint in the codebase. The equivalent would be `GET /api/v1/users/:id` but all user endpoints require valid auth (see bug below).\n\n### ⚠️ Critical Bug: JWT `id` Field Missing from Token\n**Root cause**: `token.service.js` uses `doc.id` for the JWT payload, but `auth.service.js` returns Mongoose lean docs — lean docs have `_id`, not `id`. Since `id` is `undefined`, JWT silently drops it from the token. All protected endpoints (change-password, refetch-token, all `/users/*` routes) fail with **401 Unauthorized** because `JwtStrategy` can't find the user without an `id` in the token.\n\n**Fix**: Change `doc.id` → `doc._id` in `token.service.js`'s `signToken` method.\n\n### Recommended Test Flow (once bug is fixed)\n```bash\n# 1. Login\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/signin \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Admin123!\"}'\n\n# 2. Get profile (after fixing the JWT bug)\ncurl http://localhost:3001/api/v1/users/69ddbe69e599a831d744ba89 \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer <accessToken>\"\n```"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":162,"output":881,"totalTokens":35105,"cacheRead":33444,"cacheWrite":618,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776141924250,"responseId":"062cf9652ed5c6cbe4ce20264237482d","__openclaw":{"id":"2e1a7aa9","seq":100}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:aa7da6a2-9c14-4261-b1b7-936fb3c60ec8","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","label":"DTLX BE Fix & Test","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-subagent-aa7da6a2-9c14-4261-b1b7-936fb3c60ec8","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1776141513319,"sessionId":"db466bba-5db6-4366-be8a-64512069b76f","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":56369,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"timeout","startedAt":1776140508673,"endedAt":1776141410854,"runtimeMs":0,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/db466bba-5db6-4366-be8a-64512069b76f.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"error","timestamp":1776141463551,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"df75d970","seq":215}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"error","timestamp":1776141476323,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"ffcf7