{"type":"message","id":"8b6d7745","parentId":"0aac5601","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:55:04.481Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The DTLX BE on port 3001 (the new v4 ecosystem one) is running and login works. The JWT token is returned. Let me check the token to see if `id` is present.\n\nWait - port 5555 returned nothing, meaning the old codebase (in `/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend`) is NOT running on 5555. The new one (in `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend`) is running on 3001.\n\nLet me check which workspace the 3001 server belongs to and confirm the JWT bug.","thinkingSignature":"a959113943e25fe339ad7d524f0744a172d40172b7ebb8ac3043d8ddb7da1d61"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_88f8l8zc03zl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=$(curl -s http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/signin -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Password123@\"}' | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['data']['accessToken'])\"); echo \"Token: $TOKEN\"; python3 -c \"import sys,base64; parts='$TOKEN'.split('.'); print('Payload:', base64.urlsafe_b64decode(parts[1]+'==').decode())\" 2>/dev/null; curl -s http://localhost:3001/api/v1/users/role -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" | head -c 200"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":217,"output":318,"cacheRead":49053,"cacheWrite":2745,"totalTokens":52333,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776149695072,"responseId":"062d17c1bf81ab289404945312048447"}}
