{"type":"message","id":"848d17ab","parentId":"771e7a9e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T06:55:12.770Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The JWT token DOES have the `id` field now. The payload shows `{\"id\":\"69dde49db5c07c63bb44ba89\",\"email\":\"admin2@gmail.com\",\"iat\":1776149704,\"exp\":1776236104}`. So the bug has been fixed!\n\nBut the `/users/role` endpoint returns \"Bạn không có quyền truy cập api này\" — \"You don't have permission to access this API.\" This is a permission/authorization issue, not the JWT bug.\n\nLet me test more endpoints to get a complete picture.","thinkingSignature":"afa1589e14db268b045aeca2f6251ed2467be1f36e08aacba99d433f4f6a2d70"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_18iqp8temalo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=$(curl -s http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/signin -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Password123@\"}' | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['data']['accessToken'])\")\necho \"=== Testing protected endpoints with token ===\"\nfor ep in \"/api/v1/roles\" \"/api/v1/agents\" \"/api/v1/users/role\" \"/api/v1/users/teachers\" \"/api/v1/users/students\" \"/api/v1/users/sales\" \"/api/v1/courses\" \"/api/v1/lessons\" \"/api/v1/student-infos\" \"/api/v1/work-calendars\" \"/api/v1/exams\" \"/api/v1/vehicles\" \"/api/v1/stadiums\" \"/api/v1/payments\" \"/api/v1/notify-configs\" \"/api/v1/notify-contents\"; do\n  STATUS=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:3001$ep -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\")\n  echo \"$STATUS $ep\"\ndone"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":323,"output":406,"cacheRead":51349,"cacheWrite":879,"totalTokens":52957,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776149705222,"responseId":"062d17ca7a6c3f78862448aa5b4402db"}}
