{"type":"message","id":"7d278103","parentId":"2cf12aa3","timestamp":"2026-04-15T02:49:31.778Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There it is! The old code used `mongoose.Types.ObjectId(csId)` (no `new`) while the new remote code changed to `new mongoose.Types.ObjectId(csId)` (with `new`). \n\nThe old code worked because `mongoose.Types.ObjectId(value)` as a regular function call was valid (it would create an ObjectId from the value). But the new code with `new mongoose.Types.ObjectId(value)` - TypeScript is saying it expects 0 arguments.\n\nWait, but why would `mongoose.Types.ObjectId` without `new` work but with `new` not? In TypeScript, if `mongoose.Types.ObjectId` is a constructor function, both `new mongoose.Types.ObjectId(x)` and `mongoose.Types.ObjectId(x)` should be valid (the latter implicitly creates a `new` call).\n \nLooking at the mongoose type definitions, I see that `Types.ObjectId` is actually typed as the `Schema.Types.ObjectId` class, which extends `SchemaType` and expects `(path: string, options?: any)` as its constructor signature. So when calling `new mongoose.Types.ObjectId(csId)`, TypeScript is interpreting `csId` as the `path` parameter, but the error about expecting 0 arguments suggests there's a mismatch between how the constructor is defined and how it's being called.\n\nThe real issue is likely that `mongoose.Types.ObjectId` is being exported as the `SchemaType` class rather than the `ObjectIdConstructor` from mongodb, which would explain why the constructor signature doesn't match what the code expects. The `ObjectIdConstructor` interface does have a call signature `new (s?: string | number | ObjectId): ObjectId` which should accept one argument, but TypeScript is saying \"Expected 0 arguments\". I'm wondering if `skipLibCheck: true` in the tsconfig is preventing library type checking, but that shouldn't affect user code using those types. Maybe there's a `declare module` override somewhere in the project's types that's conflicting with the mongoose definitions.","thinkingSignature":"faea1141936cd647857d4f046140f4348715f4509d157d1a28af273b5aad350a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4rqo3bvfwuip_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"declare.*module\\|declare.*mongoose\\|ObjectId\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/ --include=\"*.d.ts\" -l 2>/dev/null | head -5\nfind /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/src -name \"*.d.ts\" 2>/dev/null | head -10","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":325,"output":561,"cacheRead":50805,"cacheWrite":891,"totalTokens":52582,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776221357187,"responseId":"062e2fae7003eb7d3f7bd351d1cfb4ec"}}
