{"type":"message","id":"59110cf9","parentId":"9f394700","timestamp":"2026-04-15T03:00:50.353Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead is saying I should NOT create merge requests or push to git unless Lead explicitly says to. But in the previous task, Lead asked me to \"fetch code new\" which I interpreted as a request to sync and push. Looking at the context:\n\nLead's previous message: \"now you need fetch code new in ahv-dtlx-backend branch is clean-architecture-migration\"\nMy action: I fetched, merged, fixed TS errors, committed and pushed.\n\nBut Lead is now saying I shouldn't create MR or push unless explicitly told. This is a workflow rule clarification.\n\nActually wait - looking at the MEMORY.md Git Workflow rules:\n\n\n- **BẮT BUỘC trước khi push**: luôn `git merge origin/develop` để tránh \"commit behind\" + MR bị reject\n- Xong: tạo MR để Lead review, không tự merge\n- Chỉ Lead merge khi đã approve\n\nLead is telling me to STOP creating MRs or pushing to git automatically - these should only happen when explicitly instructed. The git workflow in MEMORY.md specifies that MRs should be created for Lead review and only Lead should merge, but the key point is that these actions require explicit authorization from Lead, not automatic execution.\n\nI should also check whether there's a `develop` branch distinction I need to be aware of, since the BE project is currently on the `feature/clean-architecture-migration` branch rather than `develop`.","thinkingSignature":"850eef5c766a3ee6247d3d8c47cc888a406bf77d4f40a45f91cfe82d76f17513"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0qh65bo46y9p_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend && git remote -v && git branch -r | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":148,"output":365,"cacheRead":10789,"cacheWrite":43979,"totalTokens":55281,"cost":{"inp